metatags.twitter:title: Florida Enacts the Digital Bill of Rights, Joining the Growing Privacy Landscape
metatags.og:title: Florida Enacts the Digital Bill of Rights, Joining the Growing Privacy Landscape | White & Case LLP
metatags.og:description: Florida Governor Ron DeSantis recently signed Senate Bill 262 into law, adopting the "Digital Bill of Rights" proposed by his office in February. Florida joins the rapidly increasing group of states, California, Utah, Colorado, Connecticut, Virginia, Iowa, Indiana, Tennessee, Montana, and Texas (together, "US State Data Privacy Laws") with comprehensive data privacy laws. The Florida Digital Bill of Rights ("FDBR") is set to take effect on July 1, 2024.
